Fishing and agriculture are the mainstays of the Central Celebes province's economy, especially in the coastal region of Donggala.
Nickel mines are also important in the province, but are mainly concentrated in Morowali, on the opposite coast of Célebes.
Palu and Donggala have been affected by tsunamis several times over the past 100 years, according to the Disaster Mitigation Agency of Indonesia.
In 1938, a tsunami killed more than 200 people and destroyed hundreds of homes in Donggala.
A tsunami also affected the western part of Donggala in 1996, causing the deaths of nine people.
