2004: A major earthquake on the western coast of Indonesia's Aceh province in northern Sumatra, which occurred on December 26, caused a tsunami that affected 14 countries, killing 226,000 people on the coast of the Indian Ocean, more than half of them in Aceh.
2005: A series of strong earthquakes hit the west coast of Sumatra in late March and early April.
