2006: A 6.8-magnitude earthquake struck southern Java, Indonesia's most populous island, causing a tsunami that devastated the southern coast, killing nearly 700 people.
2009: A 7.6-magnitude earthquake struck near the city of Padang, the capital of West Sumatra province.
More than 1,100 people died.
2010: A 7.5-magnitude earthquake struck the Mentawai Islands off Sumatra, causing a tsunami of up to 10 meters that destroyed dozens of peoples and caused the deaths of approximately 300 people.
