Red tide information: Concentrations are declining in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
According to the most recent report by the Florida Wildlife Conservation and Fisheries Commission, there is a general reduction in red tide concentrations in parts of the Tampa Bay area.
According to the aforementioned commission, increasingly unequal conditions of upwelling are being observed in the areas of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier counties, which may mean that concentrations are being reduced.
The red tide extends approximately 210 km from the coast from the northern counties of Pinellas to the southern counties of Lee.
